.TH TRIANGLE2SHAPE 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
triangle2shape \- convert PSLG files produced by Triangle back to a shapefile
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B triangle2shape
.I arealimit
.I pslg
.I shapename
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B triangle2shape
reads the PSLG files
.IR pslg .node
and
.IR pslg .poly,
reconstructs closed polygons from their edges and writes the result as
an ESRI shapefile
.RI ( shapename .shp
plus an empty
.IR .dbf ).
Polygons whose geographical area is smaller than
.I arealimit
square kilometres are dropped.
.PP
This is the final step of the shapetools amalgamation pipeline; see
.BR amalgamate (1)
for the full sequence. When the area limit was already applied during
amalgamation, pass
.B 0
here to keep every polygon.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I arealimit
Minimum polygon area in square kilometres; smaller polygons are
dropped. Use
.B 0
to keep every polygon.
.TP
.I pslg
Stem of the input PSLG files
.RI ( pslg .node ", " pslg .poly ).
.TP
.I shapename
Stem of the output shapefile.
.SH EXAMPLES
Build a shapefile from amalgamated PSLG output:
.PP
.RS 4
triangle2shape 0 suomi.1 suomishape
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shape2triangle (1),
.BR amalgamate (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-shapetools/issues>.
